					<div class="smd-orbit-loader" role="status" aria-hidden="true"><div class="orbit-plane"><span class="orbit-dot"></span></div></div><div id="post-list-container" class="hds-content-items hds-content-items-grid margin-top-2" aria-live="polite" data-rest-url="https://science.nasa.gov/wp-json/smd/v1/content-list">    <div class="hds-content-item content-list-item-nasa-blog">
                    <a href="https://science.nasa.gov/blogs/webb/2026/03/06/how-nasas-webb-helped-rule-out-asteroids-chance-of-2032-lunar-impact/" class="hds-content-item-thumbnail">
                <figure class="hds-media-background  content-list-thumbnail"><img loading="lazy" data-no-id="true" sizes="auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" srcset="https://assets.science.nasa.gov/dynamicimage/assets/science/missions/webb/blog/2025/asteroid-2024-YR4.png?fit=clip&crop=faces%2Cfocalpoint&w=300 300w" alt="" style="transform: scale(1); transform-origin: 50% 50%; object-position: 50% 50%; object-fit: cover;" src="https://assets.science.nasa.gov/dynamicimage/assets/science/missions/webb/blog/2025/asteroid-2024-YR4.png?fit=clip&#038;crop=faces%2Cfocalpoint&#038;w=300" ></figure>            </a>
                <div class="hds-content-item-inner">
            <a href="https://science.nasa.gov/blogs/webb/2026/03/06/how-nasas-webb-helped-rule-out-asteroids-chance-of-2032-lunar-impact/" class="hds-content-item-heading">
                <div class="hds-a11y-heading-22">How NASA’s Webb Helped Rule Out Asteroid’s Chance of 2032 Lunar Impact</div>
            </a>
                                                    <p class="margin-top-0 margin-bottom-1">Editor’s Note: This post highlights data from Webb science in progress, which has not yet been through the peer-review process.&hellip;</p>
                                        <div class="label margin-y-1">Mar 6, 2026</div>
                        <div class="display-flex flex-align-center label color-carbon-60 margin-bottom-auto"><svg class="square-2 margin-right-1" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" x="0px" y="0px" width="16px" height="16px" viewBox="0 0 20 20" style="enable-background:new 0 0 16 16;fill:none;"><circle cx="10" cy="10" r="9.5" stroke="#58585b"></circle><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M15 6H5V13H9L12 15V13H15V6ZM7 8H13V9H7V8ZM11 10H7V11H11V10Z" fill="#58585b"></path></svg><span>Blog</span></div>                    </div>
            </div>
        <div class="hds-content-item content-list-item-nasa-blog">
                    <a href="https://science.nasa.gov/blogs/planetary-defense/2026/03/05/new-nasa-asteroid-observations-eliminate-chance-of-2032-lunar-impact/" class="hds-content-item-thumbnail">
                <figure class="hds-media-background  content-list-thumbnail"><img loading="lazy" data-no-id="true" sizes="auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" srcset="https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/screenshot-2026-03-05-at-11-14-55-am.png?w=1024 300w" alt="" style="transform: scale(1); transform-origin: 50% 50%; object-position: 50% 50%; object-fit: cover;" src="https://science.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/screenshot-2026-03-05-at-11-14-55-am.png?w=1024" ></figure>            </a>
                <div class="hds-content-item-inner">
            <a href="https://science.nasa.gov/blogs/planetary-defense/2026/03/05/new-nasa-asteroid-observations-eliminate-chance-of-2032-lunar-impact/" class="hds-content-item-heading">
                <div class="hds-a11y-heading-22">New NASA Asteroid Observations Eliminate Chance of 2032 Lunar Impact</div>
            </a>
                                                    <p class="margin-top-0 margin-bottom-1">Using data from NASA’s James Webb Space Telescope observations collected on Feb. 18 and 26, experts from NASA’s Center for&hellip;</p>
                                        <div class="label margin-y-1">Mar 5, 2026</div>
                        <div class="display-flex flex-align-center label color-carbon-60 margin-bottom-auto"><svg class="square-2 margin-right-1" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" x="0px" y="0px" width="16px" height="16px" viewBox="0 0 20 20" style="enable-background:new 0 0 16 16;fill:none;"><circle cx="10" cy="10" r="9.5" stroke="#58585b"></circle><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M15 6H5V13H9L12 15V13H15V6ZM7 8H13V9H7V8ZM11 10H7V11H11V10Z" fill="#58585b"></path></svg><span>Blog</span></div>                    </div>
            </div>
        <div class="hds-content-item content-list-item-post">
                    <a href="https://science.nasa.gov/missions/webb/nasas-webb-examines-cranium-nebula/" class="hds-content-item-thumbnail">
                <figure class="hds-media-background  content-list-thumbnail"><img loading="lazy" data-no-id="true" sizes="auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" srcset="https://assets.science.nasa.gov/dynamicimage/assets/science/missions/webb/science/2026/02/STScI-01K843KG664WG1FD061J0AFCSH.jpg?fit=clip&crop=faces%2Cfocalpoint&w=300 300w" alt="" style="transform: scale(1); transform-origin: 50% 50%; object-position: 50% 50%; object-fit: cover;" src="https://assets.science.nasa.gov/dynamicimage/assets/science/missions/webb/science/2026/02/STScI-01K843KG664WG1FD061J0AFCSH.jpg?fit=clip&#038;crop=faces%2Cfocalpoint&#038;w=300" ></figure>            </a>
                <div class="hds-content-item-inner">
            <a href="https://science.nasa.gov/missions/webb/nasas-webb-examines-cranium-nebula/" class="hds-content-item-heading">
                <div class="hds-a11y-heading-22">NASA’s Webb Examines Cranium Nebula</div>
            </a>
                                                    <p class="margin-top-0 margin-bottom-1">Two heads are better than one in the latest images from NASA’s James Webb Space Telescope, which reveal new detail&hellip;</p>
                                        <div class="label margin-y-1">Feb 25, 2026</div>
                        <div class="display-flex flex-align-center label color-carbon-60 margin-bottom-auto"><svg version="1.1" class="square-2 margin-right-1" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" x="0px" y="0px" width="16px" height="16px" viewBox="0 0 16 16" style="enable-background:new 0 0 16 16;" xml:space="preserve"><g><g><path d="M8,0C3.5,0-0.1,3.7,0,8.2C0.1,12.5,3.6,16,8,16c4.4,0,8-3.6,8-8C16,3.5,12.4,0,8,0z M8,15.2 C4,15.2,0.8,12,0.8,8C0.8,4,4,0.8,8,0.8c3.9,0,7.2,3.2,7.2,7.1C15.2,11.9,12,15.2,8,15.2z"/><path d="M5.6,12c0.8-0.8,1.6-1.6,2.4-2.4c0.8,0.8,1.6,1.6,2.4,2.4c0-2.7,0-5.3,0-8C8.8,4,7.2,4,5.6,4 C5.6,6.7,5.6,9.3,5.6,12z"/></g></g></svg><span>Article</span></div>                    </div>
            </div>
        <div class="hds-content-item content-list-item-stma">
                    <a href="https://science.nasa.gov/asset/webb/exposed-cranium-nebula-nircam-and-miri-images/" class="hds-content-item-thumbnail">
                <figure class="hds-media-background  content-list-thumbnail"><img loading="lazy" data-no-id="true" sizes="auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" srcset="https://assets.science.nasa.gov/dynamicimage/assets/science/missions/webb/science/2026/02/STScI-01K843KG664WG1FD061J0AFCSH.jpg?fit=clip&crop=faces%2Cfocalpoint&w=300 300w" alt="" style="transform: scale(1); transform-origin: 50% 50%; object-position: 50% 50%; object-fit: cover;" src="https://assets.science.nasa.gov/dynamicimage/assets/science/missions/webb/science/2026/02/STScI-01K843KG664WG1FD061J0AFCSH.jpg?fit=clip&#038;crop=faces%2Cfocalpoint&#038;w=300" ></figure>            </a>
                <div class="hds-content-item-inner">
            <a href="https://science.nasa.gov/asset/webb/exposed-cranium-nebula-nircam-and-miri-images/" class="hds-content-item-heading">
                <div class="hds-a11y-heading-22">Exposed Cranium Nebula (NIRCam and MIRI Images)</div>
            </a>
                                                    <p class="margin-top-0 margin-bottom-1">The differences in what Webb&rsquo;s infrared instruments reveal and conceal within the PMR 1 &ldquo;Exposed Cranium&rdquo; nebula is apparent in&hellip;</p>
                                        <div class="label margin-y-1">Feb 25, 2026</div>
                        <div class="display-flex flex-align-center label color-carbon-60 margin-bottom-auto"><svg class="square-2 margin-right-1" version="1.1" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 20 20" style="enable-background:new 0 0 20 20;" xml:space="preserve"><circle cx="10" cy="10" r="9.5" stroke="#58585b" fill="#ffffff"/><path d="M15 5.99958C15 7.10421 14.1042 8 12.9996 8C11.8958 8 11 7.10421 11 5.99958C11 4.89495 11.8958 4 12.9996 4C14.1042 4 15 4.89495 15 5.99958Z" fill="#58585b"/><path d="M14 9L17 14H3.5L8 6L11.7 12.7L14 9Z" fill="#58585b"/></svg><span>Image</span></div>                    </div>
            </div>
        <div class="hds-content-item content-list-item-stma">
                    <a href="https://science.nasa.gov/asset/webb/exposed-cranium-nebula-nircam-and-miri-compass-image/" class="hds-content-item-thumbnail">
                <figure class="hds-media-background  content-list-thumbnail"><img loading="lazy" data-no-id="true" sizes="auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" srcset="https://assets.science.nasa.gov/dynamicimage/assets/science/missions/webb/science/2026/02/STScI-01K844BA1AZXKQK30F748JX5P4.jpg?fit=clip&crop=faces%2Cfocalpoint&w=300 300w" alt="" style="transform: scale(1); transform-origin: 50% 50%; object-position: 50% 50%; object-fit: cover;" src="https://assets.science.nasa.gov/dynamicimage/assets/science/missions/webb/science/2026/02/STScI-01K844BA1AZXKQK30F748JX5P4.jpg?fit=clip&#038;crop=faces%2Cfocalpoint&#038;w=300" ></figure>            </a>
                <div class="hds-content-item-inner">
            <a href="https://science.nasa.gov/asset/webb/exposed-cranium-nebula-nircam-and-miri-compass-image/" class="hds-content-item-heading">
                <div class="hds-a11y-heading-22">Exposed Cranium Nebula (NIRCam and MIRI Compass Image)</div>
            </a>
                                                    <p class="margin-top-0 margin-bottom-1">These images of the &ldquo;Exposed Cranium&rdquo; nebula PMR 1, captured by the James Webb Space Telescope&rsquo;s NIRCam (Near-Infrared Camera) and&hellip;</p>
                                        <div class="label margin-y-1">Feb 25, 2026</div>
                        <div class="display-flex flex-align-center label color-carbon-60 margin-bottom-auto"><svg class="square-2 margin-right-1" version="1.1" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 20 20" style="enable-background:new 0 0 20 20;" xml:space="preserve"><circle cx="10" cy="10" r="9.5" stroke="#58585b" fill="#ffffff"/><path d="M15 5.99958C15 7.10421 14.1042 8 12.9996 8C11.8958 8 11 7.10421 11 5.99958C11 4.89495 11.8958 4 12.9996 4C14.1042 4 15 4.89495 15 5.99958Z" fill="#58585b"/><path d="M14 9L17 14H3.5L8 6L11.7 12.7L14 9Z" fill="#58585b"/></svg><span>Image</span></div>                    </div>
            </div>
        <div class="hds-content-item content-list-item-stma">
                    <a href="https://science.nasa.gov/asset/webb/observations-of-the-exposed-cranium-nebula/" class="hds-content-item-thumbnail">
